RACE.RACE_TEXT: SANTA ANITA PARK RACE 1 6 1/2F Turf CR: 98. Starter Optional Claiming Purse 36000. FOR THREE YEAR OLDS AND UPWARD WHICH HAVE STARTED FOR A CLAIMING PRICE OF $50,000 OR LESS AND WHICH HAVE NEVER WON TWO RACES OR CLAIMING $50,000 AND WHICH HAVE NEVER WON TWO RACES. Three Year Olds, 121 lbs.; Older, 124 lbs. Claiming Price $50,000 (Horses Entered For The Allowance Are Preferred). (Rail at 30 feet).
RACE.FOOTNOTES: VIRAT bumped with outer rival at the start, went up to take control and set a pressured pace, cleared around the turn, showed the way along the inside into the lane, opened up in upper stretch and held safely under urging. EDDIE'S LAST trailed in the early going from inside, saved ground through the turn, tipped off the rail in the lane and rallied for the place. BELMONT BILL stalked three wide into the turn, chased two wide into the drive, failed to summon the needed late kick to threaten the winner in the furlong grounds and got edged for second. AWESOME RHYTHM chased from inside into and around the bend, tipped out in upper stretch and lacked a bid. MARS ON FIRE settled early outside rivals, rounded the bend three wide and failed to rally. THIRTY FOUR COUPE bumped with inner rival in the beginning, prompted the pace from outside to the turn, failed to keep up with the winner around the bend, chased a bit off the rail into the lane and weakened. VAGABOND SHOES sat off the pace three deep then off the rail, navigated the turn two then three wide and proved no menace. POWERTRAIN forwardly placed early between rivals, chased two wide still in between on the turn and came up empty in the drive.

ENTRY.NAME: Eddie's Last
ENTRY.COMMENT: trailed, inside, tipped out str, rallied for 2nd

ENTRY.NAME: Awesome Rhythm
ENTRY.COMMENT: chased inside, tipped out, no bid

ENTRY.NAME: Virat
ENTRY.COMMENT: bumped start, pace inside, kicked clear upper, held safely

ENTRY.NAME: Belmont Bill
ENTRY.OWNER: Guernsey Jade H and Osborne Candice J

RACE.RACE_TEXT: SANTA ANITA PARK RACE 2 6F Dirt CR: 80. Maiden Special Weight Purse 61000. FOR MAIDENS, FILLIES AND MARES THREE, FOUR, AND FIVE YEARS OLD. Three Year Olds, 121 lbs.; Older, 124 lbs. (Non-Starters For A Claiming Price Of $40,000 Or Less In Their Last Start Preferred).
RACE.FOOTNOTES: BANGS dueled for command between rivals early then took control leaving the backstretch, headed by RILEY G midway around the bend, fought with that rival down the stretch and held gamely to the wire. RILEY G bumped with outer rival at the start, shifted in early, raced up close three deep, pressed from outside then headed BANGS near the five-sixteenths pole, fought through the lane, drifted in and bumped BANGS at the sixteenth pole and could not get by. SIDE BY SIDE broke well and vied for command inside a pair of rivals early, chased the top pair leaving the backstretch, asked right handed leaving the bend, kept on through the lane and finished a clear third. STORMING GRAY raced outside rivals at the back, ran three wide on the turn, two wide into the stretch and proved no menace. DANCING MO drifted into the heels of RILEY G and had to steady early, traveled in the second flight along the inside into the turn, saved ground into the stretch, tipped out at the top of the lane and lacked further response. JAZZY BOO broke slow and bumped with inner rival, chased off the pace two wide into the turn, moved out to the three path then angled to the inside leaving the bend and weakened in the stretch.

ENTRY.NAME: Side by Side
ENTRY.COMMENT: broke well, vied inside, chased, clear 3rd

ENTRY.NAME: Dancing Mo
ENTRY.COMMENT: drifted/steadied early, saved ground, no response

ENTRY.NAME: Riley G
ENTRY.COMMENT: bumped start, shifted in early, up close 3deep, drifted/bmpd 1/16

RACE.RACE_TEXT: SANTA ANITA PARK RACE 3 6 1/2F Turf CR: 87. Maiden Special Weight Purse 61000. FOR MAIDENS, TWO YEARS OLD. Weight, 120 lbs. (Non-Starters For A Claiming Price Of $40,000 Or Less In Their Last Starts Preferred). (Rail at 30 feet).
RACE.FOOTNOTES: FINAL BOSS pressed the pace from outside, lost touch with the leader into the turn, chased two wide around the bend and drew closer entering the lane, took over in upper stretch, cleared at the eighth pole and lasted over the runner-up. ISLAND CRUISER broke a step slow, reserved in the early going, went two wide into the turn, angled out and came four wide into the stretch, rallied from outside and just missed. AINT NO JOKE chased from inside out of range, lost ground around the bend, remained inside to the stretch, rallied along the fence and got up for the show. RASTAMAN VIBE broke in, raced towards the rear early, went three wide into the turn, got bumped out to the four path near the five-sixteenths pole, finished willingly through the lane and got edged for third. SKETCHY traveled along the inside near the back into the turn, coaxed around the bend while tipping two wide, lacked room in traffic in upper stretch, tipped out midstretch and could not rally. WENDELSSOHN got bumped from outside leaving the gate, went up to set the pace under pressure, cleared exiting the backstretch, saved ground on the inside through the bend, tested again by FINAL BOSS and gave up command in upper stretch, then weakened in the furlong grounds. LET SEAMUS GO traveled in mid-pack outside a rival into the turn, chased two wide then moved over to the rail around the bend, steered out in the lane, lacked room entering the final sixteenth and could not regain momentum after gaining a clear path. STICK SHIFT broke in and bumped, sat off the pace early on, moved out on the turn and bumped rival at the five-sixteenths pole, got put in tight in upper stretch and weakened.

ENTRY.NAME: Stick Shift
ENTRY.OWNER: West Coast Stables LLC and Foster Thomas J
ENTRY.COMMENT: broke in/bumped, 2-3wide between, bumped 5/16, tight upper

ENTRY.NAME: Aint No Joke
ENTRY.OWNER: Slam Dunk Racing Carroll Boys Racing and McClanahan Jerry
ENTRY.COMMENT: chased inside, lost ground turn, up for 3rd

ENTRY.OWNER: Talla Racing LLC and West Point Thoroughbreds

RACE.FOOTNOTES: SHERLYN GO GO set the pace under pressure from GYPSY LYNN early, maintained a short lead two wide into the lane, shook free in upper stretch and drew off. GYPSY LYNN pressed the pace from outside into and around the bend, came three wide into the lane, lost touch with the winner in upper stretch and stayed on to secure second. ON PURPOSE stalked the top pair from outside up the backstretch, spun three wide into the lane and lacked a response when called upon. AWESOME TAYLOR settled at the back on the inside, saved ground to the stretch and failed to threaten. BACK ON THE STREET raced outside rivals in the second flight, took the turn four wide and could not make an impact. SUGAR SUGAR sat off the pace, rounded the bend two wide and was not a factor.

RACE.RACE_TEXT: SANTA ANITA PARK RACE 5 1 1/8M Turf CR: 106. Allowance Optional Claiming Purse 65000. FOR THREE YEAR OLDS AND UPWARD WHICH HAVE NEVER WON $18,000 TWICE OTHER THAN MAIDEN, CLAIMING, STARTER, OR STATE BRED OR WHICH HAVE NEVER WON THREE RACES OR CLAIMING PRICE $80,000. Claiming Price $80,000 (Horses Entered For The Allowance Are Preferred). (Rail at 30 feet).
RACE.FOOTNOTES: AVENUE bumped with outer rival at the start, unhurried in the beginning, moved closer from inside on the backstretch, pushed on through the far turn, tipped out at the top of the lane and lacked a bid. CASH EQUITY (FR) got bumped leaving the gate, stalked from inside, moved out three deep on the backstretch, chased three then two wide around that bid, bid outside the leader in upper stretch, got floated out by that rival through the lane and lacked the needed late punch to go by. ALIGATO settled outside a rival early then moved over to the inside on the clubhouse turn, went between foes in the middle stages, roused two to three wide on the far turn, tipped out in the lane and flattened. CARMELITA'S MAN raced off the pace and moved inside, tipped two wide around the clubhouse turn, trailed into the far turn, navigated that turn three then two wide and could not threaten. PERCOLATE (IRE) bobbled leaving the gate, showed early speed then ceded command to TIO MAGICO and stalked from inside, roused on the far turn and weakened in the lane. TIO MAGICO dueled briefly then cleared and moved inside, set all the pace to the stretch, challenged by CASH EQUITY (FR) in upper stretch, drifted out while maintaining a short lead through the lane and gamely prevailed.

RACE.FOOTNOTES: DON'T BRING CRAZY stalked from inside, waited for room to open on the turn, tipped out to the two path for a clear run but ran into traffic briefly at the quarter pole, swung four wide into the lane, took over in upper stretch and drew away under mild urging. CRITICISM broke well, raced up close five deep into the turn, vied three deep then led three wide outside a rival into the lane, overtaken by DON'T BRING CRAZY in upper stretch and stayed on to prove second best. PETITE ANGE stalked off the inside, had to steady into the turn, rallied three, four, then five wide around the bend but flattened in the furlong grounds. WE'LL DO IT LIVE broke a step slow, vied four deep between up the backstretch, fought in the two path through the turn and weakened in the lane. SHE'S MY NIECE showed speed three deep between rivals, got bothered past the three-eighths pole, went five wide into the lane and came up empty. BLISSTERINTHESUN got bumped leaving the gate, vied for the lead from inside then inched ahead up the backstretch, fought with outer rivals around the turn, chased those rivals into the lane and weakened. STORMY GAL broke in and bumped, vied between foes to the turn, dropped back around the bend and tired.

RACE.FOOTNOTES: DIAMONDS DANZING stalked in the two path into the turn, launched a bid from outside at the quarter pole, fought between rivals in the lane and dug in the final sixteenth to prove best. QUEEN OF POMPEII stalked four deep then had to take hold briefly when running up on heels, stalked four wide into the turn, bid three deep at the quarter pole, battled down the stretch and finished gamely to the wire. SONG OF SHADOWS sped clear quickly, moved inside for the turn, met the bid from outer rivals at the quarter pole, resisted to the sixteenth pole and yielded grudgingly late. GOLDEN AGAIN stalked the pace from inside into and around the bend, roused in the lane and could not summon the needed late kick. SENSIBLE MOVE stalked between rivals, bumped with inner foe approaching the turn, ran two to three wide around the bend, moved out for a clear run and kept on while needing to find more late. ROMAN EMPRESS stalked between foes, bumped with SENSIBLE MOVE nearing the turn, steered to the inside, angled out across the dirt and lacked a rally. DON'T JU FORGET broke a step slow and inward, raced off the pace two wide into the turn, came out across the dirt and failed to menace. HOT ROD MAMA came in early, lagged behind to the stretch and was not a factor.

RACE.FOOTNOTES: BLESSED ANGEL broke out and brushed with outer rival, showed speed inside BLACKENED then switched to the outside to give chase, drew alongside and headed that rival on the turn, fought two wide to the stretch, cleared with a furlong remaining and drew away. WARREN'S SHOW BIZZ lacked early speed, trailed on the inside then two wide on the turn, moved in at the eighth pole, steered back out some and closed belatedly to nail BLACKENED for second. BLACKENED cleared inner rival and crossed to the inside, dueled with BLESSED ANGLE around the bend, could not keep pace with the winner at the furlong marker and got nailed for second. ILA VEIW TOO chased two wide into the turn, traveled between runners around the bend, asked right handed three wide into the stretch and failed to respond. LIKE NO OTHER brushed from inside at the start, chased three deep between rivals into and around the bend and lacked a rally. PAID IN GOLD stumbled a bit while breaking quickest then dropped back to a tracking position four deep, remained four wide through the turn and came up empty in the lane. ROPERS N WRANGLERS stalked the pace from inside, moved out in the lane and weakened.
